theorem closure_union_interior_closure_eq_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    closure ((A : Set X) ∪ interior (closure (A : Set X))) =
      closure (A : Set X) := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `⊆` : the union is contained in `closure A`, hence so is its closure.
    have hSub :
        ((A : Set X) ∪ interior (closure (A : Set X)) : Set X) ⊆
          closure (A : Set X) := by
      intro x hx
      cases hx with
      | inl hA =>
          exact subset_closure hA
      | inr hInt =>
          exact (interior_subset : interior (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆
            closure (A : Set X)) hInt
    exact closure_mono hSub
  · -- `⊇` : since `A ⊆` the union, the closure of `A` is contained in the closure of the union.
    have hSub :
        (A : Set X) ⊆ ((A : Set X) ∪ interior (closure (A : Set X))) := by
      intro x hx
      exact Or.inl hx
    exact closure_mono hSub

import Mathlib

open Set

theorem closure_union_interior_closure_eq_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure ((A ∪ interior (closure (A : Set X))) : Set X) = closure (A : Set X) := by
  -- Left-to-right inclusion.
  have h₁ :
      (A ∪ interior (closure (A : Set X)) : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
    intro x hx
    cases hx with
    | inl hxA     => exact subset_closure hxA
    | inr hxInt   =>
        have : interior (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) :=
          interior_subset
        exact this hxInt
  have h_left : closure ((A ∪ interior (closure (A : Set X))) : Set X) ⊆
      closure (A : Set X) := closure_mono h₁

  -- Right-to-left inclusion.
  have h₂ : (A : Set X) ⊆ A ∪ interior (closure (A : Set X)) := by
    intro x hxA
    exact Or.inl hxA
  have h_right : closure (A : Set X) ⊆
      closure ((A ∪ interior (closure (A : Set X))) : Set X) :=
    closure_mono h₂

  exact Set.Subset.antisymm h_left h_right

theorem closure_interior_closure_eq_closure_of_P1 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 A →
      closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) = closure (A : Set X) := by
  intro hP1
  -- First inclusion: `closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A`.
  have h₁ :
      closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
    have : (interior (closure (A : Set X)) : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) :=
      interior_subset
    exact closure_mono this
  -- Second inclusion: `closure A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A))`.
  have hEq :
      closure (A : Set X) = closure (interior (A : Set X)) :=
    (Topology.P1_iff_closure_eq_closure_interior (X := X) (A := A)).1 hP1
  have h₂ :
      closure (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆
        closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) := by
    apply closure_mono
    have : (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆ interior (closure (A : Set X)) :=
      interior_mono (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X))
    exact this
  have h₃ :
      closure (A : Set X) ⊆
        closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) := by
    simpa [hEq] using h₂
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm h₁ h₃

theorem interior_subset_interior_union_left
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (A ∪ B : Set X) := by
  exact interior_mono (Set.subset_union_left : (A : Set X) ⊆ A ∪ B)
